---
title: Mexicali Black Bean Soup with the Works
description: This week, we’re serving a hearty, flavorful black bean soup that’s ready in just 20 minutes—and it all cooks up in one pot, making cleanup a breeze! The beans are simmered in a richly-spiced broth with diced tomatoes, veggie stock, onion, tomato paste, and Southwest seasonings until the soup is thick and the beans are tender. For toppings, load up your bowl with “the works”—scallions, cheddar cheese, smoky red pepper crema, and crushed blue corn tortilla chips. Now that’s what we call a truly SOUP-er supper.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/mexicali-black-bean-soup-ffd1c12c.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/mexicali-black-bean-soup-608022d5e8b2b21b26654652-06bf61b9.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/mexicali-black-bean-soup-608022d5e8b2b21b26654652
course: main course
time required: 20 minutes
cuisine: Mexican
nutrition:
  calories: 620 kcal
  fat: 26 g
  saturated fat: 9 g
  carbohydrates: 68 g
  sugar: 13 g
  protein: 22 g
  fiber: 12 g
  sodium: 1800 mg
author: Michelle Doll Olson
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and finely dice @yellow onion{1} until you have
¾ cup (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings). Trim and thinly slice
@scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Dice @Roma tomato{1}.
Drain @black beans{13.4%oz} over a #small bowl{}, reserving liquid.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a large #pot{} over
medium-high heat. Add onion and scallion whites. Cook, stirring,
until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add @Southwest spice blend{1%tbsp}; stir until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in diced tomato, @tomato paste{1.5%oz}, and @Tex-Mex paste{1}
until slightly darkened in color, ~{1%minute}.

Stir @water{1 3/4%cups}, @veggie stock concentrate{2}, beans, and ¼ cup
reserved bean liquid into pot. (For 4 servings, use 3 cups water and
½ cup bean liquid.) Bring to a boil and cook, stirring occasionally,
until thickened, ~{5-8%minutes}.

> Prefer your broth a bit thicker? Simmer a little longer—or vice versa!
> You're the chef, after all.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Turn off heat.

Crush a few @blue corn tortilla chips{1.5%oz} in a #bowl{}.

Divide soup between #bowls{} and top with scallion greens, @cheddar
cheese{½%cup}, @smoky red pepper crema{2%tbsp}, and as many crushed
tortilla chips as you like. Serve with whole tortilla chips on the side.

> TIP: Start with a few crushed chips and add more as you go to keep them crunchy!